   "source": [
    "## Calibration 1 — step length (decision D10)\n",
    "\n",
    "The step length started as a guess (0.70 m) but made the estimated path far too\n",
    "long. Measuring a clean, straight, single-floor corridor leg against the door\n",
    "references gives the real step length: `distance / number_of_steps`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "b6d30a70",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-07-07T12:57:13.194975Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-07-07T12:57:13.194886Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-07-07T12:57:13.277932Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-07-07T12:57:13.277680Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "corridor distance   : 27.0 m\n",
      "steps during the leg : 67\n",
      "implied step length  : 0.40 m\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import building\n",
    "import evaluation\n",
    "\n",
    "# The reference workbook lives under ../assignment when running from notebooks/.\n",
    "reference = evaluation.load_reference(1, reference_file=\"../assignment/Paths_references.xlsx\")\n",
    "doors = building.door_positions()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run 1's first floor-0 leg runs from door 024 to door 018.\n",
    "t_start = reference[(reference[\"floor\"] == 0) & (reference[\"room\"] == \"24\")].iloc[0][\"t_rel\"]\n",
    "t_end = reference[(reference[\"floor\"] == 0) & (reference[\"room\"] == \"18\")].iloc[0][\"t_rel\"]\n",
    "distance = abs(doors[(0, \"18\")][0] - doors[(0, \"24\")][0])\n",
    "leg_steps = steps[(steps[\"t_rel\"] >= t_start) & (steps[\"t_rel\"] <= t_end)]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"corridor distance   : %.1f m\" % distance)\n",
    "print(\"steps during the leg : %d\" % len(leg_steps))\n",
    "print(\"implied step length  : %.2f m\" % (distance / len(leg_steps)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "249a4603",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Doing this for every run gives implied step lengths of about **0.40–0.53 m** on\n",
    "Runs 1, 3, 4 (Run 2's short leg under-counts and is an outlier). We adopt a single\n",
    "calibrated constant of **0.50 m**, which roughly halved the door-checkpoint error\n",
    "on every run. See decision D10."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3c0fef85",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Calibration 2 — per-run initial heading (decision D11)\n",
    "\n",
    "The gyro gives only *relative* heading; its absolute anchor depends on how the\n",
    "phone sat in the pocket (an unknown per-run yaw offset). Leaving it at 0 (east) for\n",
    "every run launched non-eastward runs the wrong way. We calibrate the initial\n",
    "heading by aligning each run's first straight corridor leg to the known corridor\n",
    "axis, and store the result in `preprocessing.RUN_START`."
   ]
